215 BOOLEAN WmipIsQuerySetGuid(
216  PBGUIDENTRY GuidEntry
217  )
218 {
219  PLIST_ENTRY InstanceSetList;
220  PBINSTANCESET InstanceSet;
221 
222  PAGED_CODE();
223 
224  WmipAssert(GuidEntry != NULL);
225 
226  WmipEnterSMCritSection();
227  InstanceSetList = GuidEntry->ISHead.Flink;
228  while (InstanceSetList != &GuidEntry->ISHead)
229  {
230  InstanceSet = CONTAINING_RECORD(InstanceSetList,
231  INSTANCESET,
232  GuidISList);
233  if ( (InstanceSet->Flags &
234  (IS_TRACED | IS_CONTROL_GUID | IS_EVENT_ONLY)) == 0 )
235  {
236  //
237  // If there is at least one IS that isn't traced and isn't
238  // an event only then it is a queryset guid
239  //
240  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
241  return (TRUE);
242  }
243  InstanceSetList = InstanceSetList->Flink;
244  }
245  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
246 
247  return (FALSE);
248 
249 }

252 NTSTATUS WmipOpenBlock(
253  IN ULONG Ioctl,
254  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
255  IN POBJECT_ATTRIBUTES CapturedObjectAttributes,
256  IN ULONG DesiredAccess,
257  OUT PHANDLE Handle
258  )
259 {
260  PBGUIDENTRY GuidEntry;
261  PWMIGUIDOBJECT Object;
262  NTSTATUS Status;
263 
264  PAGED_CODE();
265 
266  //
267  // Creates a guid handle with the desired access
268  //
269  Status = WmipOpenGuidObject(CapturedObjectAttributes,
270  DesiredAccess,
271  AccessMode,
272  Handle,
273  &Object);
274 
275 
276  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
277  {
278  Object->Type = Ioctl;
279 
280  if (Ioctl != IOCTL_WMI_OPEN_GUID)
281  {
282  GuidEntry = WmipFindGEByGuid(&Object->Guid, FALSE);
283 
284  //
285  // Establish our object on the guidentry list
286  //
287  WmipEnterSMCritSection();
288  if (GuidEntry != NULL)
289  {
290  InsertTailList(&GuidEntry->ObjectHead,
291  &Object->GEObjectList);
292 
293  }
294  Object->GuidEntry = GuidEntry;
295  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
296 
297  switch (Ioctl)
298  {
299  case IOCTL_WMI_OPEN_GUID_FOR_QUERYSET:
300  {
301  //
302  // Guid is being opened for query/set/method operations so
303  // we need to ensure that there is a guid entry and that
304  // the guid entry has InstanceSets attached and it is
305  // has at least one instance set that is not a traced
306  // guid and is not an event only guid
307  //
308  if ((GuidEntry == NULL) ||
309  (GuidEntry->ISCount == 0) ||
310  (! WmipIsQuerySetGuid(GuidEntry)))
311  {
312  //
313  // Either we could not find a guidentry or there
314  // is no instance sets attached. We close the
315  // original handle and fail the IOCTL
316  //
317  ZwClose(*Handle);
318  Status = STATUS_WMI_GUID_NOT_FOUND;
319  break;
320  }
321  //
322  // Fall through
323  //
324  }
325 
326  case IOCTL_WMI_OPEN_GUID_FOR_EVENTS:
327  {
328  //
329  // Since we can register to receive events before
330  // the event provider has been registered we'll need
331  // to create the guid entry if one does not exist
332  //
333 
334  if (AccessMode == KernelMode)
335  {
336  Object->Flags |= WMIGUID_FLAG_KERNEL_NOTIFICATION;
337  }
338 
339  if (GuidEntry == NULL)
340  {
341  WmipAssert(Ioctl == IOCTL_WMI_OPEN_GUID_FOR_EVENTS);
342 
343  WmipEnterSMCritSection();
344  GuidEntry = WmipAllocGuidEntry();
345  if (GuidEntry != NULL)
346  {
347  //
348  // Initialize the new GuidEntry and place it
349  // on the master GuidEntry list.
350  //
351  memcpy(&GuidEntry->Guid,
352  &Object->Guid,
353  sizeof(GUID));
354 
355  InsertHeadList(WmipGEHeadPtr, &GuidEntry->MainGEList);
356  InsertTailList(&GuidEntry->ObjectHead,
357  &Object->GEObjectList);
358  Object->GuidEntry = GuidEntry;
359  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
360  } else {
361  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
362  ZwClose(*Handle);
363  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
364  break;
365  }
366  }
367 
368 
369  //
370  // Now we need to see if we have to enable collection
371  // or events
372  //
373  Status = WmipEnableCollectOrEvent(GuidEntry,
374  Ioctl,
375  &Object->EnableRequestSent,
376  0);
377 
378  if (! NT_SUCCESS(Status))
379  {
380  //
381  // For some reason enabling failed so just return
382  // the error
383  //
384  ZwClose(*Handle);
385  }
386 
387  //
388  // Don't unref the guid entry as that ref count is
389  // taken by the object just placed on the list
390  //
391  break;
392  }
393 
394  default:
395  {
396  //
397  // We should never get here.....
398  //
399  WmipAssert(FALSE);
400 
401  ZwClose(*Handle);
402  Status = STATUS_ILLEGAL_FUNCTION;
403  break;
404  }
405  }
406  } else {
407  //
408  // Mark this as a security object
409  //
410  Object->Flags |= WMIGUID_FLAG_SECURITY_OBJECT;
411  }
412 
413  //
414  // remove the ref taken when the object was created
415  //
416  ObDereferenceObject(Object);
417  }
418  return(Status);
419 }

423 NTSTATUS WmipAddProviderIdToPIList(
424  PBINSTANCESET **PIPtrPtr,
425  PULONG PICountPtr,
426  PULONG PIMaxPtr,
427  PBINSTANCESET *StaticPIPtr,
428  PBINSTANCESET InstanceSet
429 )
430 {
431  ULONG PICount;
432  ULONG PIMax, NewPIMax;
433  PBINSTANCESET *PIPtr, *OldPIPtr, *NewPIPtr;
434  NTSTATUS Status;
435  ULONG i;
436 
437  PAGED_CODE();
438 
439  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
440  PICount = *PICountPtr;
441  PIMax = *PIMaxPtr;
442  PIPtr = *PIPtrPtr;
443 
444  //
445  // Remember dynamic providerid
446  //
447  if (PICount == PIMax)
448  {
449  //
450  // We have overflowed the PI List so we need to
451  // reallocate a bigger buffer
452  //
453  NewPIMax = PIMax * 2;
454  NewPIPtr = (PBINSTANCESET *)WmipAlloc(NewPIMax *
455  sizeof(PBINSTANCESET));
456  OldPIPtr = PIPtr;
457  if (NewPIPtr != NULL)
458  {
459  //
460  // Copy provider ids from old to new buffer
461  //
462  memcpy(NewPIPtr, OldPIPtr, PIMax*sizeof(PBINSTANCESET));
463  PIPtr = NewPIPtr;
464  *PIPtrPtr = NewPIPtr;
465  PIMax = NewPIMax;
466  *PIMaxPtr = PIMax;
467  } else {
468  //
469  // Bad break, we could not allocate more space
470  // unref any instance sets and return an error
471  //
472  for (i = 0; i < PIMax; i++)
473  {
474  WmipUnreferenceIS(PIPtr[i]);
475  }
476  WmipUnreferenceIS(InstanceSet);
477  *PIPtrPtr = NULL;
478 
479  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
480  }
481 
482  //
483  // if previous buffer was not static then free it
484  //
485  if (OldPIPtr != StaticPIPtr)
486  {
487  WmipFree(OldPIPtr);
488  }
489  }
490 
491  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
492  {
493  //
494  // Remember instance set
495  //
496  PIPtr[PICount++] = InstanceSet;
497  *PICountPtr = PICount;
498  }
499  return(Status);
500 }

502 NTSTATUS WmipPrepareForWnodeAD(
503  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT GuidObject,
504  OUT LPGUID Guid,
505  IN OUT ULONG *ProviderIdCount,
506  OUT PBINSTANCESET **ProviderIdList,
507  OUT BOOLEAN *InternalGuid
508  )
509 {
510  PBINSTANCESET *PIPtr, *StaticPIPtr;
511  ULONG PICount, PIMax;
512  NTSTATUS Status;
513  PBGUIDENTRY GuidEntry;
514  PBINSTANCESET InstanceSet;
515  PLIST_ENTRY InstanceSetList;
516 
517  PAGED_CODE();
518 
519  GuidEntry = GuidObject->GuidEntry;
520 
521  if ((GuidEntry != NULL) && (GuidEntry->ISCount > 0))
522  {
523  //
524  // We were passed a valid guid handle, get out the guid
525  //
526  *Guid = GuidEntry->Guid;
527 
528  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
529  if (GuidEntry->Flags & GE_FLAG_INTERNAL)
530  {
531  *InternalGuid = TRUE;
532  } else {
533  //
534  // Build list of provider ids to whom the QAD will be targetted
535  //
536  *InternalGuid = FALSE;
537 
538  StaticPIPtr = *ProviderIdList;
539  PIPtr = StaticPIPtr;
540  PIMax = *ProviderIdCount;
541  PICount = 0;
542 
543  WmipEnterSMCritSection();
544 
545  InstanceSetList = GuidEntry->ISHead.Flink;
546  while ((InstanceSetList != &GuidEntry->ISHead) &&
547  NT_SUCCESS(Status))
548  {
549  InstanceSet = CONTAINING_RECORD(InstanceSetList,
550  INSTANCESET,
551  GuidISList);
552 
553  //
554  // Take a refcount on the instance set so that it won't
555  // go away until after we are done with our query
556  // The refcount gets removed by the caller when it is
557  // done with the list or in WmipAddProviderIdTOLlist if it
558  // returns an error
559  //
560 
561  if ((InstanceSet->Flags & (IS_TRACED | IS_CONTROL_GUID | IS_EVENT_ONLY)) == 0)
562  {
563  //
564  // Only take those IS that are not traced or control
565  // guids and are not event only guids
566  //
567  WmipReferenceIS(InstanceSet);
568  Status = WmipAddProviderIdToPIList(&PIPtr,
569  &PICount,
570  &PIMax,
571  StaticPIPtr,
572  InstanceSet);
573  }
574 
575  InstanceSetList = InstanceSetList->Flink;
576  }
577 
578  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
579 
580  if (PICount == 0)
581  {
582  Status = STATUS_WMI_GUID_DISCONNECTED;
583  } else {
584  *ProviderIdCount = PICount;
585  *ProviderIdList = PIPtr;
586  }
587  }
588  } else {
589  Status = STATUS_WMI_GUID_DISCONNECTED;
590  }
591 
592  return(Status);
593 }

597 ULONG WmipStaticInstanceNameSize(
598  PBINSTANCESET InstanceSet
599  )
600 /*+++
601 
602 Routine Description:
603 
604  This routine will calculate the size needed to place instance names in
605  a WNODE_ALL_DATA
606 
607 Arguments:
608 
609  WmiInstanceInfo describes to instance set whose instance name size
610  is to be calculated
611 
612 Return Value:
613 
614  Size needed to place instance names in a WNODE_ALL_DATA plus 3. The
615  extra 3 bytes are added in case the OffsetInstanceNameOffsets need to be
616  padded since they must be on a 4 byte boundary.
617 
618 ---*/
619 {
620  SIZE_T NameSize;
621  ULONG i;
622 
623  PAGED_CODE();
624 
625  //
626  // If we already computed this then just return the results
627  if (InstanceSet->WADInstanceNameSize != 0)
628  {
629  return(InstanceSet->WADInstanceNameSize);
630  }
631 
632  //
633  // Start with a name size of 3 in case the OffsetInstanceNameOffset will
634  // need to be padded so that it starts on a 4 byte boundary.
635  NameSize = 3;
636 
637  if (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_BASENAME)
638  {
639  //
640  // For static base names we assume that there will never be more than
641  // MAXBASENAMESUFFIXVALUE instances of a guid. So the size of each instance name
642  // would be the size of the base name plus the size of the suffix
643  // plus a USHORT for the count (for counted string) plus a ULONG
644  // to hold the offset to the instance name
645  //
646  WmipAssert((InstanceSet->IsBaseName->BaseIndex + InstanceSet->Count) < MAXBASENAMESUFFIXVALUE);
647 
648  NameSize += ((wcslen(InstanceSet->IsBaseName->BaseName) * sizeof(WCHAR)) +
649  MAXBASENAMESUFFIXLENGTH * sizeof(WCHAR) +
650  sizeof(USHORT) +
651  sizeof(ULONG)) * InstanceSet->Count;
652 
653  } else if (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_STATICNAMES)
654  {
655  //
656  // For a static name list we count up each size of
657  // the static instance names in the list and add a ULONG and a USHORT
658  // for the offset and count (for counted string)
659  for (i = 0; i < InstanceSet->Count; i++)
660  {
661  NameSize += (wcslen(InstanceSet->IsStaticNames->StaticNamePtr[i]) + 2) * sizeof(WCHAR) + sizeof(ULONG);
662  }
663  }
664 
665  InstanceSet->WADInstanceNameSize = (ULONG)NameSize;
666 
667  return(ULONG)(NameSize);
668 }
669 
670 void WmipInsertStaticNames(
671  PWNODE_ALL_DATA Wnode,
672  ULONG MaxWnodeSize,
673  PBINSTANCESET InstanceSet
674  )
675 /*+++
676 
677 Routine Description:
678 
679  This routine will copy into the WNODE_ALL_DATA instance names for a
680  static instance name set. If the Wnode_All_data is too small then it
681  is converted to a WNODE_TOO_SMALL
682 
683 Arguments:
684 
685  Wnode points at the WNODE_ALL_DATA
686  MaxWnodeSize is the maximum size of the Wnode
687  WmiInstanceInfo is the Instance Info
688 
689 Return Value:
690 
691 ---*/
692 {
693  PWCHAR NamePtr;
694  PULONG NameOffsetPtr;
695  ULONG InstanceCount;
696  ULONG i;
697  WCHAR Index[MAXBASENAMESUFFIXLENGTH+1];
698  PWCHAR StaticName;
699  ULONG SizeNeeded;
700  SIZE_T NameLen;
701  USHORT Len;
702  ULONG PaddedBufferSize;
703  size_t Size;
704  HRESULT hr;
705 
706  PAGED_CODE();
707 
708  if ((InstanceSet->Flags &
709  (IS_INSTANCE_BASENAME | IS_INSTANCE_STATICNAMES)) == 0)
710  {
711  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,"WMI: Try to setup static names for dynamic guid\n"));
712  return;
713  }
714  InstanceCount = InstanceSet->Count;
715 
716  //
717  // Pad out the size of the incoming wnode to a 4 byte boundary since the
718  // OffsetInstanceNameOffsets is being appended to the end of the
719  // wnode and it must be on a 4 byte boundary
720  //
721  PaddedBufferSize = (Wnode->WnodeHeader.BufferSize + 3) & ~3;
722 
723  //
724  // Compute the complete size needed to rewrite the WNODE to include
725  // the instance names.
726  //
727  // Include the size that is needed to fill out
728  Size = WmipStaticInstanceNameSize(InstanceSet);
729 
730  // Include the space needed for the array of offsets to the
731  // instance names plus the size of the names plus the padded
732  // size of the wnode
733  SizeNeeded = (InstanceCount * sizeof(ULONG)) +
734  (ULONG)Size +
735  PaddedBufferSize;
736 
737  if (SizeNeeded > MaxWnodeSize)
738  {
739  //
740  // If not enough space left in the buffer passed then build a
741  // WNODE_TOO_SMALL as the result to indicate how much buffer
742  // space is needed.
743  //
744  Wnode->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
745  Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags = WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL;
746  ((PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)Wnode)->SizeNeeded = SizeNeeded;
747  return;
748  }
749 
750  //
751  // Allocate space for the array of offsets to instance names
752  //
753  NameOffsetPtr = (PULONG)((PUCHAR)Wnode + PaddedBufferSize);
754  Wnode->OffsetInstanceNameOffsets = (ULONG)((PUCHAR)NameOffsetPtr - (PUCHAR)Wnode);
755 
756  //
757  // Point at the beginning of the area to write the instance names
758  //
759  NamePtr = (PWCHAR)(NameOffsetPtr + InstanceCount);
760 
761 
762  if (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_BASENAME)
763  {
764  //
765  // The instance name is based upon a basename with a trailing
766  // index number to provide uniqueness
767  //
768  if (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_PDO_INSTANCENAME)
769  {
770  Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags |= WNODE_FLAG_PDO_INSTANCE_NAMES;
771  }
772 
773  for (i = 0; i < InstanceCount; i++)
774  {
775  //
776  // Account for space used by length of string that follows
777  //
778  Size -= sizeof(USHORT);
779  *NameOffsetPtr++ = (ULONG)((PUCHAR)NamePtr - (PUCHAR)Wnode);
780 
781  //
782  // Copy over basename while accounting length used by it
783  //
784  hr = StringCbCopy(NamePtr+1,
785  Size,
786  InstanceSet->IsBaseName->BaseName);
787  WmipAssert(hr == S_OK);
788 
789  //
790  // Format unique index number
791  //
792  hr = StringCbPrintf(Index,
793  sizeof(Index),
794  BASENAMEFORMATSTRING,
795  InstanceSet->IsBaseName->BaseIndex+i);
796  WmipAssert(hr == S_OK);
797 
798  //
799  // Append unique index number to instance name
800  //
801  hr = StringCbCat(NamePtr+1,
802  Size,
803  Index);
804  WmipAssert(hr == S_OK);
805 
806  NameLen = wcslen(NamePtr+1) + 1;
807  *NamePtr = (USHORT)NameLen * sizeof(WCHAR);
808  NamePtr += NameLen + 1;
809 
810  Size -= NameLen * sizeof(WCHAR);
811  }
812  } else if (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_STATICNAMES) {
813  //
814  // Instance names are from a list of static names
815  //
816  for (i = 0; i < InstanceCount; i++)
817  {
818  *NameOffsetPtr++ = (ULONG)((PUCHAR)NamePtr - (PUCHAR)Wnode);
819  StaticName = InstanceSet->IsStaticNames->StaticNamePtr[i];
820  Len = (USHORT)((wcslen(StaticName)+1) * sizeof(WCHAR));
821  *NamePtr++ = Len;
822 
823  //
824  // Account for space used by length of string that follows
825  //
826  Size -= sizeof(USHORT);
827 
828  //
829  // Copy over and account for static name
830  //
831  hr = StringCbCopyEx(NamePtr,
832  Size,
833  StaticName,
834  NULL,
835  &Size,
836  0);
837  WmipAssert(hr == S_OK);
838 
839  NamePtr += Len / sizeof(WCHAR);
840 
841  }
842  }
843  Wnode->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = SizeNeeded;
844 }
845 
846 
847 
848 //
849 // This defines how many provider ids will fit within the static block. If
850 // we need more than this, then we'll have to allocate memory for it
851 //
852 #if DBG
853 #define MANYPROVIDERIDS 1
854 #else
855 #define MANYPROVIDERIDS 16
856 #endif
857 
858 NTSTATUS WmipQueryAllData(
859  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT GuidObject,
860  IN PIRP Irp,
861  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
862  IN PWNODE_ALL_DATA Wnode,
863  IN ULONG OutBufferLen,
864  OUT PULONG RetSize
865  )
866 {
867  NTSTATUS Status;
868  PBINSTANCESET StaticPIList[MANYPROVIDERIDS];
869  PBINSTANCESET *PIList;
870  PBINSTANCESET InstanceSet;
871  WNODE_ALL_DATA WnodeAllData;
872  BOOLEAN IsBufferTooSmall;
873  PWNODE_HEADER WnodeHeader;
874  LOGICAL UsesStaticNames;
875  PWNODE_TOO_SMALL WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)&WnodeAllData;
876  PWNODE_ALL_DATA WnodeAD;
877  ULONG BufferLeft;
878  ULONG SizeNeeded;
879  ULONG PICount;
880  ULONG WnodeFlags, WnodeSize;
881  PWNODE_HEADER WnodeLast;
882  ULONG Linkage;
883  ULONG i;
884  GUID Guid;
885  PUCHAR Buffer;
886  ULONG BufferUsed;
887  HANDLE KernelHandle;
888  BOOLEAN InternalGuid;
889  IO_STATUS_BLOCK Iosb;
890 
891  PAGED_CODE();
892 
893  //
894  // Check Security
895  //
896  if (GuidObject != NULL)
897  {
898  Status = ObReferenceObjectByPointer(GuidObject,
899  WMIGUID_QUERY,
900  WmipGuidObjectType,
901  AccessMode);
902  } else {
903  KernelHandle = Wnode->WnodeHeader.KernelHandle;
904 
905  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle(KernelHandle,
906  WMIGUID_QUERY,
907  WmipGuidObjectType,
908  AccessMode,
909  &GuidObject,
910  NULL);
911  }
912 
913  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
914  {
915  //
916  // Get the provider id list for the guid
917  //
918  PIList = StaticPIList;
919  PICount = MANYPROVIDERIDS;
920  Status = WmipPrepareForWnodeAD(GuidObject,
921  &Guid,
922  &PICount,
923  &PIList,
924  &InternalGuid);
925  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
926  {
927  if (InternalGuid)
928  {
929  //
930  // This is an internal guid so we fill out the WNODE_ALL_DATA
931  // and mark it to be completed by the user mode code
932  //
933  Wnode->WnodeHeader.Guid = Guid;
934  Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags |= WNODE_FLAG_INTERNAL;
935  Wnode->WnodeHeader.Linkage = 0;
936  *RetSize = sizeof(WNODE_HEADER);
937  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
938  } else {
939  //
940  // Get all of the information from the WNODE_HEADER so we can
941  // rebuild it
942  //
943  WnodeFlags = Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags;
944  WnodeSize = Wnode->WnodeHeader.BufferSize;
945 
946  //
947  // Loop over all provider ids and send each a WAD query
948  //
949  Buffer = (PUCHAR)Wnode;
950  BufferLeft = OutBufferLen;
951  IsBufferTooSmall = FALSE;
952  SizeNeeded = 0;
953  WnodeLast = NULL;
954  for (i = 0; i < PICount; i++)
955  {
956  InstanceSet = PIList[i];
957 
958  if ((IsBufferTooSmall) || (BufferLeft < sizeof(WNODE_ALL_DATA)))
959  {
960  //
961  // If we have already determined that the buffer is
962  // too small then we use the static WNODE_ALL_DATA
963  // just to get the size needed
964  //
965  WnodeAD = &WnodeAllData;
966  BufferLeft = sizeof(WNODE_ALL_DATA);
967  IsBufferTooSmall = TRUE;
968  } else {
969  //
970  // Otherwise we will append to the end of the buffer
971  //
972  WnodeAD = (PWNODE_ALL_DATA)Buffer;
973  }
974 
975  //
976  // Build the WNODE and send it off to the driver
977  //
978  WnodeHeader = (PWNODE_HEADER)WnodeAD;
979  WnodeHeader->BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_HEADER);
980  UsesStaticNames =((InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_BASENAME) ||
981  (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_STATICNAMES));
982  WnodeHeader->Flags = WnodeFlags | (UsesStaticNames ?
983  WNODE_FLAG_STATIC_INSTANCE_NAMES :
984  0);
985  WnodeHeader->Guid = Guid;
986  WnodeHeader->ProviderId = PIList[i]->ProviderId;
987  WnodeHeader->Linkage = 0;
988 
989  if (Irp != NULL)
990  {
991  Status = WmipForwardWmiIrp(Irp,
992  IRP_MN_QUERY_ALL_DATA,
993  WnodeHeader->ProviderId,
994  &WnodeHeader->Guid,
995  BufferLeft,
996  WnodeAD);
997  } else {
998  Status = WmipSendWmiIrp(
999  IRP_MN_QUERY_ALL_DATA,
1000  WnodeHeader->ProviderId,
1001  &WnodeHeader->Guid,
1002  BufferLeft,
1003  WnodeAD,
1004  &Iosb);
1005  }
1006 
1007  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
1008  {
1009  if (WnodeHeader->Flags & WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL)
1010  {
1011  //
1012  // There was not enough space to write the WNODE
1013  // so we keep track of how much was needed and then
1014  // switch to the mode where we just query for size needed
1015  //
1016  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)WnodeAD;
1017 
1018  SizeNeeded += WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded;
1019  if (UsesStaticNames)
1020  {
1021  SizeNeeded = (SizeNeeded + 3) &~3;
1022  SizeNeeded += WmipStaticInstanceNameSize(InstanceSet)+
1023  (InstanceSet->Count *sizeof(ULONG));
1024  }
1025 
1026  SizeNeeded = (SizeNeeded +7) & ~7;
1027 
1028  IsBufferTooSmall = TRUE;
1029  } else if (IsBufferTooSmall) {
1030  //
1031  // We passed a minimum sized buffer, but it is large
1032  // enough for the driver. Since we are just trying
1033  // to get the size needed we get the size he needs
1034  // and throw away his data
1035  //
1036  SizeNeeded += WnodeAD->WnodeHeader.BufferSize +
1037  WmipStaticInstanceNameSize(InstanceSet) +
1038  (InstanceSet->Count *sizeof(ULONG));
1039  SizeNeeded = (SizeNeeded +7) & ~7;
1040 
1041  } else {
1042  //
1043  // The driver returned a completed WNODE_ALL_DATA
1044  // so we need to link the previous WNODE_ALL_DATA to
1045  // this one, fill out any static instance names, and
1046  // then update the buffer pointer and size
1047  //
1048  if (WnodeLast != NULL)
1049  {
1050  Linkage = (ULONG) ((PCHAR)WnodeAD - (PCHAR)WnodeLast);
1051  WnodeLast->Linkage = Linkage;
1052  }
1053  WnodeLast = (PWNODE_HEADER)WnodeAD;
1054 
1055  if (UsesStaticNames)
1056  {
1057  //
1058  // We need to insert the static names
1059  //
1060  WmipInsertStaticNames(WnodeAD,
1061  BufferLeft,
1062  InstanceSet);
1063 
1064  if (WnodeAD->WnodeHeader.Flags & WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL)
1065  {
1066  //
1067  // The static names caused us to run out of
1068  // buffer so we switch to mode where we
1069  // query for the sizes
1070  //
1071  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)WnodeAD;
1072  IsBufferTooSmall = TRUE;
1073  BufferUsed = WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded;
1074  } else {
1075  //
1076  // Static names fit so just pull out the updated
1077  // wnode size
1078  //
1079  BufferUsed = WnodeAD->WnodeHeader.BufferSize;
1080  }
1081  } else {
1082  //
1083  // Wnode has dynamic names so just add size returned
1084  // by driver
1085  //
1086  BufferUsed = WnodeAD->WnodeHeader.BufferSize;
1087  }
1088 
1089  //
1090  // Update size needed and advance to free space in
1091  // output buffer
1092  //
1093  BufferUsed = (BufferUsed + 7) & ~7;
1094  SizeNeeded += BufferUsed;
1095 
1096  //
1097  // Make sure that by adding in pad we don't run out of
1098  // room in buffer
1099  //
1100  if ((! IsBufferTooSmall) && (BufferLeft >= BufferUsed))
1101  {
1102  BufferLeft -= BufferUsed;
1103  Buffer += BufferUsed;
1104  } else {
1105  IsBufferTooSmall = TRUE;
1106  }
1107  }
1108  } else {
1109  //
1110  // The driver failed the request, but that is no biggie
1111  // as we just ignore it for now
1112  //
1113  }
1114 
1115  //
1116  // We are done with the instance set so remove our ref
1117  // on it so it can go away if need be
1118  //
1119  WmipUnreferenceIS(InstanceSet);
1120  }
1121 
1122  if (SizeNeeded == 0)
1123  {
1124  //
1125  // No devices responded to the WMI Query All Data so we
1126  // return an error
1127  //
1128  Status = STATUS_WMI_GUID_NOT_FOUND;
1129  } else if ((IsBufferTooSmall) &&
1130  (SizeNeeded > OutBufferLen)) {
1131  //
1132  // Our buffer passed was too small so return a WNODE_TOO_SMALL
1133  //
1134  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)Wnode;
1135  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
1136  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.Flags = WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL;
1137  WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded = SizeNeeded;
1138  *RetSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
1139  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1140  } else {
1141  *RetSize = SizeNeeded;
1142  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1143  }
1144 
1145  //
1146  // Make sure any memory allocated for the PI list is freed
1147  //
1148  if ((PIList != StaticPIList) && (PIList != NULL))
1149  {
1150  WmipFree(PIList);
1151  }
1152  }
1153  }
1154  //
1155  // And remove ref on guid object
1156  //
1157  ObDereferenceObject(GuidObject);
1158  }
1159 
1160  return(Status);
1161 }
1162 
1163 NTSTATUS WmipQueryAllDataMultiple(
1164  IN ULONG ObjectCount,
1165  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT *ObjectList,
1166  IN PIRP Irp,
1167  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
1168  IN OUT PUCHAR BufferPtr,
1169  IN ULONG BufferSize,
1170  IN PWMIQADMULTIPLE QadMultiple,
1171  OUT ULONG *ReturnSize
1172  )
1173 {
1174  ULONG i;
1175  HANDLE *Handles;
1176  ULONG Count;
1177  WNODE_ALL_DATA WnodeAD;
1178  BOOLEAN BufferOverFlow;
1179  ULONG SkipSize, RetSize, SizeNeeded;
1180  ULONG WnodeSize;
1181  NTSTATUS Status, Status2;
1182  ULONG Linkage = 0;
1183  PWNODE_TOO_SMALL WnodeTooSmall;
1184  PWNODE_HEADER WnodePrev;
1185  PUCHAR Buffer;
1186  PWNODE_ALL_DATA Wnode;
1187  PWMIGUIDOBJECT Object = NULL;
1188 
1189  PAGED_CODE();
1190 
1191  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1192 
1193  if (ObjectList == NULL) {
1194 
1195  WmipAssert(QadMultiple != NULL);
1196  WmipAssert(QadMultiple->HandleCount > 0);
1197 
1198  //
1199  // Copy the handle list out of the system buffer since it will
1200  // be overwritten by the first query all data
1201  //
1202  Count = QadMultiple->HandleCount;
1203  Handles = (HANDLE *)WmipAlloc(Count * sizeof(HANDLE));
1204 
1205  if (Handles != NULL)
1206  {
1207  for (i = 0; i < Count; i++)
1208  {
1209  Handles[i] = QadMultiple->Handles[i].Handle;
1210  }
1211 
1212  } else {
1213  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1214  }
1215  } else {
1216 
1217  WmipAssert(ObjectCount > 0);
1218 
1219  Count = ObjectCount;
1220  Handles = NULL;
1221  }
1222 
1223  SizeNeeded = 0;
1224  Buffer = BufferPtr;
1225 
1226  BufferOverFlow = FALSE;
1227  WnodePrev = NULL;
1228  Wnode = (PWNODE_ALL_DATA)Buffer;
1229  WnodeSize = BufferSize;
1230 
1231  for (i = 0; i < Count; i++)
1232  {
1233  if ((Wnode == &WnodeAD) || (WnodeSize < sizeof(WNODE_ALL_DATA)))
1234  {
1235  //
1236  // If there is no more room, we are just querying for the
1237  // size that will be needed.
1238  //
1239  Wnode = &WnodeAD;
1240  WnodeSize = sizeof(WNODE_ALL_DATA);
1241  WnodePrev = NULL;
1242  } else {
1243  Wnode = (PWNODE_ALL_DATA)Buffer;
1244  WnodeSize = BufferSize;
1245  }
1246 
1247  //
1248  // Build WNODE_ALL_DATA in order to do the query
1249  //
1250  RtlZeroMemory(Wnode, sizeof(WNODE_ALL_DATA));
1251  Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags = WNODE_FLAG_ALL_DATA;
1252  Wnode->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_HEADER);
1253 
1254  if (ObjectList == NULL)
1255  {
1256  Wnode->WnodeHeader.KernelHandle = Handles[i];
1257  } else {
1258  Object = ObjectList[i];
1259  }
1260 
1261  Status2 = WmipQueryAllData(Object,
1262  Irp,
1263  AccessMode,
1264  Wnode,
1265  WnodeSize,
1266  &RetSize);
1267 
1268  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status2))
1269  {
1270  if (Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags & WNODE_FLAG_INTERNAL)
1271  {
1272  //
1273  // Skip any internal guid quesries
1274  //
1275  } else if (Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags & WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL) {
1276  //
1277  // There is no enough room so just tally up
1278  // the size that will be needed.
1279  //
1280  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)Wnode;
1281  SizeNeeded += (WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded+7) & ~7;
1282  Wnode = &WnodeAD;
1283  BufferOverFlow = TRUE;
1284  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,"WMI: %x Too Small %x needed, total %x\n",
1285  ObjectList ? ObjectList[i] : Handles[i],
1286  WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded, SizeNeeded));
1287  } else if (Wnode == &WnodeAD) {
1288  //
1289  // Even though this succeeded, we still aren't going
1290  // to be able to return any data so just count up
1291  // how much size we need
1292  //
1293  SizeNeeded += (RetSize+7) & ~7;
1294  BufferOverFlow = TRUE;
1295 
1296  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID,
1297  DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,"WMI: %x Large Enough but full %x needed, total %x\n",
1298  ObjectList ? ObjectList[i] : Handles[i],
1299  RetSize, SizeNeeded));
1300 
1301  } else {
1302  //
1303  // We successfully got data. Link the previous wnode
1304  // to this one
1305  //
1306  if (WnodePrev != NULL)
1307  {
1308  WnodePrev->Linkage = Linkage;
1309  }
1310 
1311  WnodePrev = (PWNODE_HEADER)Wnode;
1312  while (WnodePrev->Linkage != 0)
1313  {
1314  WnodePrev = (PWNODE_HEADER)OffsetToPtr(WnodePrev,
1315  WnodePrev->Linkage);
1316  }
1317 
1318  SkipSize = (RetSize+7) &~7;
1319  SizeNeeded += SkipSize;
1320  BufferSize -= SkipSize;
1321  Buffer += SkipSize;
1322 
1323  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,"WMI: %x Large Enough %x needed, total %x\n",
1324  ObjectList ? ObjectList[i] : Handles[i],
1325  RetSize, SizeNeeded));
1326 
1327  Linkage = (ULONG) ((PCHAR)Buffer - (PCHAR)WnodePrev);
1328  }
1329  } else {
1330  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,"WMI: %x Failed %x, total %x\n",
1331  ObjectList ? ObjectList[i] : Handles[i],
1332  Status2,
1333  SizeNeeded));
1334  }
1335  }
1336 
1337  if (Handles != NULL)
1338  {
1339  WmipFree(Handles);
1340  }
1341 
1342  if (BufferOverFlow)
1343  {
1344  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)BufferPtr;
1345  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
1346  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.Flags = WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL;
1347  WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded = SizeNeeded;
1348  *ReturnSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
1349  } else {
1350  *ReturnSize = SizeNeeded;
1351  }
1352 
1353  return(Status);
1354 }
1355 
1356 NTSTATUS WmipPrepareWnodeSI(
1357  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT GuidObject,
1358  IN OUT PWNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE WnodeSI,
1359  IN OUT ULONG *ProviderIdCount,
1360  OUT PBINSTANCESET **ProviderIdList,
1361  OUT BOOLEAN *IsDynamic,
1362  OUT BOOLEAN *InternalGuid
1363  )
1364 {
1365  NTSTATUS Status;
1366  PBGUIDENTRY GuidEntry;
1367  ULONG i;
1368  PWNODE_HEADER Wnode;
1369  PWCHAR CInstanceName;
1370  PWCHAR InstanceName;
1371  PLIST_ENTRY InstanceSetList;
1372  PBINSTANCESET InstanceSet;
1373  PBINSTANCESET *PIPtr = NULL;
1374  PBINSTANCESET *StaticPIPtr = NULL;
1375  ULONG PICount = 0, PIMax;
1376  BOOLEAN Done;
1377 
1378  PAGED_CODE();
1379 
1380  *IsDynamic = TRUE;
1381  GuidEntry = GuidObject->GuidEntry;
1382  Wnode = (PWNODE_HEADER)WnodeSI;
1383 
1384  if ((GuidEntry != NULL) && (GuidEntry->ISCount > 0))
1385  {
1386  //
1387  // We were passed a valid guid handle, fill out the guid
1388  // in WNODE_HEADER
1389  //
1390  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1391  Wnode->Guid = GuidEntry->Guid;
1392 
1393  if (GuidEntry->Flags & GE_FLAG_INTERNAL)
1394  {
1395  *InternalGuid = TRUE;
1396  } else {
1397  *InternalGuid = FALSE;
1398 
1399  //
1400  // Obtain instance name from WNODE
1401  //
1402  CInstanceName = (PWCHAR)OffsetToPtr(WnodeSI,
1403  WnodeSI->OffsetInstanceName);
1404  InstanceName = WmipCountedToSz(CInstanceName);
1405  if (InstanceName != NULL)
1406  {
1407  //
1408  // Remember the static provider id list and assume that the
1409  // request is going to be dynamic
1410  //
1411  StaticPIPtr = *ProviderIdList;
1412  PIPtr = StaticPIPtr;
1413  PIMax = *ProviderIdCount;
1414  PICount = 0;
1415 
1416  //
1417  // March down instance set list to see if we have a
1418  // static name and build the list of dynamic provider ids
1419  //
1420  Done = FALSE;
1421 
1422  WmipEnterSMCritSection();
1423  if (GuidEntry->ISCount > 0)
1424  {
1425  InstanceSetList = GuidEntry->ISHead.Flink;
1426  while ((InstanceSetList != &GuidEntry->ISHead) && ! Done)
1427  {
1428  InstanceSet = CONTAINING_RECORD(InstanceSetList,
1429  INSTANCESET,
1430  GuidISList);
1431 
1432  if ((InstanceSet->Flags & (IS_TRACED | IS_CONTROL_GUID | IS_EVENT_ONLY)) == 0)
1433  {
1434  //
1435  // Only take those IS that are not traced or control
1436  // guids and are not event only guids
1437  //
1438  if (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_BASENAME)
1439  {
1440  PBISBASENAME IsBaseName;
1441  ULONG BaseIndex;
1442  PWCHAR BaseName;
1443  SIZE_T BaseNameLen;
1444  PWCHAR SuffixPtr;
1445  ULONG Suffix;
1446  WCHAR SuffixText[MAXBASENAMESUFFIXLENGTH+1];
1447 
1448  //
1449  // See if the instance name is from this base name
1450  //
1451  IsBaseName = InstanceSet->IsBaseName;
1452 
1453  BaseIndex = IsBaseName->BaseIndex;
1454  BaseName = IsBaseName->BaseName;
1455  BaseNameLen = wcslen(BaseName);
1456 
1457  if ((wcslen(InstanceName) > BaseNameLen) &&
1458  (_wcsnicmp(InstanceName, BaseName, BaseNameLen) == 0))
1459  {
1460  //
1461  // The suffix matches the beginning of our instance
1462  // name and our instance name is longer than the
1463  // suffix.
1464  //
1465  SuffixPtr = &InstanceName[BaseNameLen];
1466  Suffix = _wtoi(SuffixPtr);
1467  if ((WmipIsNumber(SuffixPtr) &&
1468  (Suffix >= BaseIndex) &&
1469  (Suffix < (BaseIndex + InstanceSet->Count))))
1470  {
1471  //
1472  // Our suffix is a number within the range for
1473  // this instance set
1474  //
1475  if (Suffix < MAXBASENAMESUFFIXVALUE)
1476  {
1477  StringCbPrintf(SuffixText,
1478  sizeof(SuffixText),
1479  BASENAMEFORMATSTRING,
1480  Suffix);
1481  if (_wcsicmp(SuffixText, SuffixPtr) == 0)
1482  {
1483  //
1484  // Our instance name is part of the
1485  // instance set so note the provider id
1486  // and instance index
1487  //
1488  Wnode->Flags |= WNODE_FLAG_STATIC_INSTANCE_NAMES;
1489  Wnode->ProviderId = InstanceSet->ProviderId;
1490  WnodeSI->InstanceIndex = Suffix - BaseIndex;
1491  *IsDynamic = FALSE;
1492  Done = TRUE;
1493  }
1494  }
1495  }
1496  }
1497  } else if (InstanceSet->Flags & IS_INSTANCE_STATICNAMES) {
1498  //
1499  // See if the passed instance name matches any of the
1500  // static names for this instance set
1501  //
1502  PWCHAR *StaticNames;
1503 
1504  StaticNames = InstanceSet->IsStaticNames->StaticNamePtr;
1505  for (i =0; i < InstanceSet->Count; i++)
1506  {
1507  if (_wcsicmp(StaticNames[i], InstanceName) == 0)
1508  {
1509  //
1510  // We matched our instance name with a static
1511  // instance name. Remember provider id and
1512  // instance index.
1513  //
1514  Wnode->Flags |= WNODE_FLAG_STATIC_INSTANCE_NAMES;
1515  Wnode->ProviderId = InstanceSet->ProviderId;
1516  WnodeSI->InstanceIndex = i;
1517  *IsDynamic = FALSE;
1518  Done = TRUE;
1519  break;
1520  }
1521  }
1522 
1523  } else {
1524  //
1525  // Remember dynamic providerid
1526  //
1527  WmipReferenceIS(InstanceSet);
1528  Status = WmipAddProviderIdToPIList(&PIPtr,
1529  &PICount,
1530  &PIMax,
1531  StaticPIPtr,
1532  InstanceSet);
1533  if (! NT_SUCCESS(Status))
1534  {
1535  Done = TRUE;
1536  }
1537  }
1538  }
1539  InstanceSetList = InstanceSetList->Flink;
1540  }
1541  } else {
1542  //
1543  // There are no instance sets registered for this guid
1544  //
1545  Status = STATUS_WMI_GUID_DISCONNECTED;
1546  }
1547 
1548  WmipFree(InstanceName);
1549  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
1550  } else {
1551  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1552  }
1553 
1554 
1555  if (*IsDynamic)
1556  {
1557  //
1558  // Dynamic instance name so return list of dynamic providers
1559  //
1560  *ProviderIdCount = PICount;
1561  *ProviderIdList = PIPtr;
1562  } else {
1563  //
1564  // Static instance name so unref an dynamic instance sets
1565  //
1566  if (PIPtr != NULL)
1567  {
1568  for (i = 0; i < PICount; i++)
1569  {
1570  WmipUnreferenceIS(PIPtr[i]);
1571  }
1572 
1573  if (PIPtr != StaticPIPtr)
1574  {
1575  WmipFree(PIPtr);
1576  }
1577  }
1578  }
1579  }
1580  } else {
1581  Status = STATUS_WMI_GUID_DISCONNECTED;
1582  }
1583 
1584  return(Status);
1585 }

1587 #ifdef ALLOC_DATA_PRAGMA
1588 #pragma const_seg("PAGECONST")
1589 #endif

1591 const ACCESS_MASK DesiredAccessForFunction[] =
1592 {

1594  WMIGUID_QUERY, // IRP_MN_QUERY_SINGLE_INSTANCE
1595  WMIGUID_SET, // IRP_MN_CHANGE_SINGLE_INSTANCE
1596  WMIGUID_SET, // IRP_MN_CHANGE_SINGLE_ITEM
1597  0, // IRP_MN_ENABLE_EVENTS
1598  0, // IRP_MN_DISABLE_EVENTS
1599  0, // IRP_MN_ENABLE_COLLECTION
1600  0, // IRP_MN_DISABLE_COLLECTION

1602  WMIGUID_EXECUTE, // IRP_MN_EXECUTE_METHOD
1603  0, // IRP_MN_TRACE_EVENT or IRP_MN_SET_TRACE_NOTIFY
1604  0 // IRP_MN_REGINFO_EX

1607 NTSTATUS WmipQuerySetExecuteSI(
1608  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT GuidObject,
1609  IN PIRP Irp,
1610  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
1611  IN UCHAR MinorFunction,
1612  IN OUT PWNODE_HEADER Wnode,
1613  IN ULONG OutBufferSize,
1614  OUT PULONG RetSize
1615  )
1616 {
1617  NTSTATUS Status, ReturnStatus;
1618  PBINSTANCESET StaticPIList[MANYPROVIDERIDS];
1619  PBINSTANCESET *PIList;
1620  HANDLE KernelHandle;
1621  ULONG PICount;
1622  BOOLEAN IsDynamic;
1623  ULONG i;
1624  BOOLEAN InternalGuid;
1625  IO_STATUS_BLOCK Iosb;
1626 
1627  PAGED_CODE();
1628 
1629  WmipAssert(((MinorFunction >= IRP_MN_QUERY_ALL_DATA) &&
1630  (MinorFunction <= IRP_MN_CHANGE_SINGLE_ITEM)) ||
1631  (MinorFunction == IRP_MN_EXECUTE_METHOD));
1632 
1633 
1634  //
1635  // Check Security
1636  //
1637  if (GuidObject != NULL)
1638  {
1639  Status = ObReferenceObjectByPointer(GuidObject,
1640  DesiredAccessForFunction[MinorFunction],
1641  WmipGuidObjectType,
1642  AccessMode);
1643  } else {
1644  KernelHandle = Wnode->KernelHandle;
1645  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle(KernelHandle,
1646  DesiredAccessForFunction[MinorFunction],
1647  WmipGuidObjectType,
1648  AccessMode,
1649  &GuidObject,
1650  NULL);
1651  }
1652 
1653  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
1654  {
1655  PIList = StaticPIList;
1656  PICount = MANYPROVIDERIDS;
1657  Status = WmipPrepareWnodeSI(GuidObject,
1658  (PWNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE)Wnode,
1659  &PICount,
1660  &PIList,
1661  &IsDynamic,
1662  &InternalGuid);
1663 
1664  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,
1665  "WMI: QSI Prepare [%s - %s] %x with %x PI at %p\n",
1666  IsDynamic ? "Dynamic" : "Static",
1667  InternalGuid ? "Internal" : "External",
1668  Wnode->KernelHandle, PICount, PIList));
1669 
1670  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
1671  {
1672  if (InternalGuid)
1673  {
1674  //
1675  // Internal guid query
1676  //
1677  Wnode->Flags |= WNODE_FLAG_INTERNAL;
1678  Wnode->BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_HEADER);
1679  Irp->IoStatus.Information = sizeof(WNODE_HEADER);
1680  } else {
1681  if (IsDynamic)
1682  {
1683  //
1684  // We need to loop over all dynamic instance names until
1685  // one of them responds successfully and then we assume
1686  // that they own the instance
1687  //
1688 
1689  if ((MinorFunction == IRP_MN_CHANGE_SINGLE_ITEM) ||
1690  (MinorFunction == IRP_MN_EXECUTE_METHOD))
1691  {
1692  Status = STATUS_WMI_ITEMID_NOT_FOUND;
1693  } else {
1694  Status = STATUS_WMI_INSTANCE_NOT_FOUND;
1695  }
1696 
1697  for (i = 0; i < PICount; i++)
1698  {
1699  Wnode->ProviderId = PIList[i]->ProviderId;
1700  if (Irp != NULL)
1701  {
1702  ReturnStatus = WmipForwardWmiIrp(Irp,
1703  MinorFunction,
1704  Wnode->ProviderId,
1705  &Wnode->Guid,
1706  OutBufferSize,
1707  Wnode);
1708 
1709  if (NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus))
1710  {
1711  *RetSize = (ULONG)Irp->IoStatus.Information;
1712  }
1713  } else {
1714  ReturnStatus = WmipSendWmiIrp(
1715  MinorFunction,
1716  Wnode->ProviderId,
1717  &Wnode->Guid,
1718  OutBufferSize,
1719  Wnode,
1720  &Iosb);
1721 
1722  if (NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus))
1723  {
1724  *RetSize = (ULONG)Iosb.Information;
1725  }
1726  }
1727 
1728  //
1729  // One of these status codes imply that the device does
1730  // positively claim the instance name and so we break out
1731  // and return the results
1732  //
1733  if ((NT_SUCCESS(ReturnStatus)) ||
1734  (ReturnStatus == STATUS_WMI_SET_FAILURE) ||
1735  (ReturnStatus == STATUS_WMI_ITEMID_NOT_FOUND) ||
1736  (ReturnStatus == STATUS_WMI_READ_ONLY))
1737  {
1738  Status = ReturnStatus;
1739  break;
1740  }
1741 
1742 
1743  //
1744  // If the device does not own the instance it can
1745  // only return STATUS_WMI_INSTANCE_NOT_FOUND or
1746  // STATUS_WMI_GUID_NOT_FOUND. Any other return code
1747  // implies that the device owns the instance, but
1748  // encountered an error.
1749  //
1750  if ( (ReturnStatus != STATUS_WMI_INSTANCE_NOT_FOUND) &&
1751  (ReturnStatus != STATUS_WMI_GUID_NOT_FOUND))
1752  {
1753  Status = ReturnStatus;
1754  }
1755  }
1756 
1757  //
1758  // Unreference each of the dynamic instance sets.
1759  //
1760 
1761  for (i = 0; i < PICount; ++i) {
1762  WmipUnreferenceIS(PIList[i]);
1763  }
1764 
1765  if ((PIList != StaticPIList) && (PIList != NULL))
1766  {
1767  WmipFree(PIList);
1768  }
1769  } else {
1770  //
1771  // Since we have a static instance name we can target directly
1772  // at the device that has our instance name
1773  //
1774  if (Irp != NULL)
1775  {
1776  Status = WmipForwardWmiIrp(Irp,
1777  MinorFunction,
1778  Wnode->ProviderId,
1779  &Wnode->Guid,
1780  OutBufferSize,
1781  Wnode);
1782 
1783  *RetSize = (ULONG)Irp->IoStatus.Information;
1784  } else {
1785  Status = WmipSendWmiIrp(
1786  MinorFunction,
1787  Wnode->ProviderId,
1788  &Wnode->Guid,
1789  OutBufferSize,
1790  Wnode,
1791  &Iosb);
1792 
1793  *RetSize = (ULONG)Iosb.Information;
1794  }
1795  }
1796  }
1797  }
1798 
1799  //
1800  // And remove ref on guid object
1801  //
1802  ObDereferenceObject(GuidObject);
1803  }
1804 
1805  return(Status);
1806 }

1808 NTSTATUS WmipQuerySingleMultiple(
1809  IN PIRP Irp,
1810  IN KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
1811  IN OUT PUCHAR BufferPtr,
1812  IN ULONG BufferSize,
1813  IN PWMIQSIMULTIPLE QsiMultiple,
1814  IN ULONG QueryCount,
1815  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT *ObjectList,
1816  IN PUNICODE_STRING InstanceNames,
1817  OUT ULONG *ReturnSize
1818  )
1819 {
1820  PWMIQSIINFO QsiInfo;
1821  ULONG WnodeQSISize;
1822  ULONG WnodeSizeNeeded;
1823  NTSTATUS Status, Status2;
1824  ULONG SizeNeeded;
1825  BOOLEAN BufferFull, BufferOverFlow;
1826  PWNODE_HEADER WnodePrev;
1827  PUCHAR Buffer;
1828  ULONG i;
1829  ULONG WnodeSize;
1830  PWNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE Wnode;
1831  PWCHAR InstanceName;
1832  ULONG RetSize;

1835  ULONG SkipSize;
1836  PWMIGUIDOBJECT Object = NULL;
1837  UNICODE_STRING UString;
1838  HANDLE KernelHandle;
1839  PWNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE WnodeQSIPtr;
1840 
1841  union {
1842  WNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE Wnode;
1843  UCHAR Buffer[sizeof(WNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE) + (256 * sizeof(WCHAR)) + sizeof(ULONG)];
1844  } WnodeQSIStatic;
1845 
1846  PAGED_CODE();
1847 
1848  WmipAssert(QueryCount > 0);
1849 
1850  //
1851  // We are called by kernel mode and passed an object list and InstanceNames
1852  // or we are called by user mode and passed a QsiMultiple instead
1853  //
1854 
1855  WmipAssert( ((AccessMode == KernelMode) &&
1856  (QsiMultiple == NULL) &&
1857  (ObjectList != NULL) &&
1858  (InstanceNames != NULL)) ||
1859  ((AccessMode == UserMode) &&
1860  (QsiMultiple != NULL) &&
1861  (ObjectList == NULL) &&
1862  (InstanceNames == NULL)) );
1863 
1864  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1865  if (ObjectList == NULL)
1866  {
1867  //
1868  // if this is a user call then we need to copy out the
1869  // QSIMULTIPLE information since it is in the system buffer and
1870  // will get overwritten on the first query
1871  //
1872  QsiInfo = (PWMIQSIINFO)WmipAlloc(QueryCount * sizeof(WMIQSIINFO));
1873 
1874  if (QsiInfo != NULL)
1875  {
1876  RtlCopyMemory(QsiInfo,
1877  &QsiMultiple->QsiInfo,
1878  QueryCount * sizeof(WMIQSIINFO));
1879  } else {
1880  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1881  }
1882  Object = NULL;
1883  } else {
1884  QsiInfo = NULL;
1885  }
1886 
1887  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
1888  {
1889  SizeNeeded = 0;
1890  BufferFull = FALSE;
1891  BufferOverFlow = FALSE;
1892  WnodePrev = NULL;
1893  Buffer = BufferPtr;
1894 
1895  WnodeQSIPtr = &WnodeQSIStatic.Wnode;
1896  WnodeQSISize = sizeof(WnodeQSIStatic.Buffer);
1897 
1898  for (i = 0; i < QueryCount; i++)
1899  {
1900  if (ObjectList == NULL)
1901  {
1902  UString.Length = QsiInfo[i].InstanceName.Length;
1903  UString.MaximumLength = QsiInfo[i].InstanceName.MaximumLength;
1904  UString.Buffer = QsiInfo[i].InstanceName.Buffer;
1905  KernelHandle = QsiInfo[i].Handle.Handle;
1906  } else {
1907  UString = InstanceNames[i];
1908  Object = ObjectList[i];
1909  KernelHandle = NULL;
1910  }
1911 
1912  WnodeSizeNeeded = (FIELD_OFFSET(WNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE,
1913  VariableData) +
1914  UString.Length +
1915  sizeof(USHORT) + 7) & ~7;
1916 
1917  if ((BufferFull) || (BufferSize < WnodeSizeNeeded))
1918  {
1919  //
1920  // If there is no more room, we are just querying for the
1921  // size that will be needed.
1922  //
1923  if (WnodeSizeNeeded > WnodeQSISize)
1924  {
1925  //
1926  // Our temporary buffer is too small so lets alloc a
1927  // larger one
1928  //
1929  if (WnodeQSIPtr != &WnodeQSIStatic.Wnode)
1930  {
1931  WmipFree(WnodeQSIPtr);
1932  }
1933 
1934  WnodeQSIPtr = (PWNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE)WmipAllocNP(WnodeSizeNeeded);
1935 
1936  if (WnodeQSIPtr == NULL)
1937  {
1938  //
1939  // We couldn't allocate a larger temporary buffer
1940  // so we abort this call and try to exit gracefully
1941  //
1942  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1943  break;
1944  }
1945 
1946  WnodeQSISize = WnodeSizeNeeded;
1947  }
1948 
1949  Wnode = WnodeQSIPtr;
1950  WnodeSize = WnodeSizeNeeded;
1951  WnodePrev = NULL;
1952  BufferFull = TRUE;
1953  } else {
1954  //
1955  // Plenty of room so build wnode directly into the output
1956  // buffer
1957  //
1958  Wnode = (PWNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE)Buffer;
1959  WnodeSize = BufferSize;
1960  }
1961 
1962  //
1963  // Build WNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE in order to do the query
1964  //
1965  RtlZeroMemory(Wnode, sizeof(WNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE));
1966  Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags = WNODE_FLAG_SINGLE_INSTANCE;
1967  Wnode->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = WnodeSizeNeeded;
1968  Wnode->WnodeHeader.KernelHandle = KernelHandle;
1969 
1970  Wnode->OffsetInstanceName = FIELD_OFFSET(WNODE_SINGLE_INSTANCE,
1971  VariableData);
1972  Wnode->DataBlockOffset = WnodeSizeNeeded;
1973  InstanceName = (PWCHAR)OffsetToPtr(Wnode,
1974  Wnode->OffsetInstanceName);
1975 
1976 
1977  *InstanceName++ = UString.Length;
1978  try
1979  {
1980  if (AccessMode == UserMode)
1981  {
1982  ProbeForRead(UString.Buffer,
1983  UString.Length,
1984  sizeof(WCHAR));
1985  }
1986 
1987  RtlCopyMemory(InstanceName,
1988  UString.Buffer,
1989  UString.Length);
1990 
1991 
1992  } except(EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1993  //
1994  // If an error occured probing then we fail the entire call
1995  //
1996  Status = GetExceptionCode();
1997  break;
1998  }
1999 
2000 
2001  Status2 = WmipQuerySetExecuteSI(Object,
2002  Irp,
2003  AccessMode,
2004  IRP_MN_QUERY_SINGLE_INSTANCE,
2005  (PWNODE_HEADER)Wnode,
2006  WnodeSize,
2007  &RetSize);
2008 
2009  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status2))
2010  {
2011  if (Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags & WNODE_FLAG_INTERNAL)
2012  {
2013  //
2014  // Skip any internal guid quesries
2015  //
2016  } else if (Wnode->WnodeHeader.Flags & WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL) {
2017  //
2018  // There is no enough room so just tally up
2019  // the size that will be needed.
2020  //
2021  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)Wnode;
2022  SizeNeeded += (WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded+7) & ~7;
2023  BufferFull = TRUE;
2024  BufferOverFlow = TRUE;
2025  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,
2026  "WMI: QSIM %ws too small %x SizeNeeded %x\n",
2027  UString.Buffer,
2028  (WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded+7) & ~7,
2029  SizeNeeded));
2030  } else if (BufferFull) {
2031  //
2032  // There was enough room, but the buffer was already
2033  // filled so we just tally up the size needed
2034  //
2035  SizeNeeded += (RetSize+7) & ~7;
2036  BufferOverFlow = TRUE;
2037  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,
2038  "WMI: QSIM %ws big enough but full %x SizeNeeded %x\n",
2039  UString.Buffer,
2040  (RetSize+7) & ~7,
2041  SizeNeeded));
2042  } else {
2043  //
2044  // We successfully got data. Link the previous wnode
2045  // to this one
2046  //
2047  if (WnodePrev != NULL)
2048  {
2049  WnodePrev->Linkage = Linkage;
2050  }
2051 
2052  WnodePrev = (PWNODE_HEADER)Wnode;
2053  while (WnodePrev->Linkage != 0)
2054  {
2055  WnodePrev = (PWNODE_HEADER)OffsetToPtr(WnodePrev,
2056  WnodePrev->Linkage);
2057  }
2058 
2059  SkipSize = (RetSize+7) &~7;
2060  SizeNeeded += SkipSize;
2061  BufferSize -= SkipSize;
2062  Buffer += SkipSize;
2063 
2064  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,
2065  "WMI: QSIM %ws big enough %x SizeNeeded %x\n",
2066  UString.Buffer,
2067  SkipSize,
2068  SizeNeeded));
2069 
2070  Linkage = (ULONG) ((PCHAR)Buffer - (PCHAR)WnodePrev);
2071  }
2072  } else {
2073  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_API_INFO_LEVEL,
2074  "WMI: QSIM %ws Failed SizeNeeded %x\n",
2075  UString.Buffer,
2076  SizeNeeded));
2077  }
2078  }
2079 
2080  if (WnodeQSIPtr != &WnodeQSIStatic.Wnode)
2081  {
2082  WmipFree(WnodeQSIPtr);
2083  }
2084 
2085  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status) && (BufferFull))
2086  {
2087  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)BufferPtr;
2088  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
2089  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.Flags = WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL;
2090  WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded = SizeNeeded;
2091  *ReturnSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
2092  } else {
2093  *ReturnSize = SizeNeeded;
2094  }
2095 
2096  if (QsiInfo != NULL)
2097  {
2098  WmipFree(QsiInfo);
2099  }
2100  }
2101 
2102  return(Status);
2103 }

2486 void WmipCopyFromEventQueues(
2487  IN POBJECT_EVENT_INFO ObjectArray,
2488  IN ULONG HandleCount,
2489  OUT PUCHAR OutBuffer,
2490  OUT ULONG *OutBufferSizeUsed,
2491  OUT PWNODE_HEADER *LastWnode,
2492  IN BOOLEAN IsHiPriority
2493  )
2494 {
2495 
2496  PWMIGUIDOBJECT GuidObject;
2497  ULONG i, Earliest;
2498  ULONG SizeUsed, Size;
2499  PWNODE_HEADER InWnode, OutWnode;
2500  LARGE_INTEGER Timestamp, LastTimestamp;
2501  PWMIEVENTQUEUE EventQueue;
2502 
2503 
2504  //
2505  // Consider adding extra code for perf
2506  // 1. If only 1 object is passed
2507  // 2. Once we find the earliest event we look ahead in that same
2508  // event queue buffer assuming that it will be earlier than
2509  // events in other buffers. This makes sense when only one queue
2510  // has events left in it.
2511  //
2512 
2513  PAGED_CODE();
2514 
2515  //
2516  // This routine assumes that the output buffer has been checked and
2517  // that it is large enough to accommodate all of the events. This
2518  // implies that this function is called while holding the critical
2519  // section.
2520  //
2521 
2522  //
2523  // See which guid objects have events to be processed
2524  //
2525  for (i = 0; i < HandleCount; i++)
2526  {
2527  GuidObject = ObjectArray[i].GuidObject;
2528  if (IsHiPriority)
2529  {
2530  if ((GuidObject->HiPriority.Buffer != NULL) &&
2531  (GuidObject->HiPriority.NextOffset != 0))
2532  {
2533  ObjectArray[i].NextWnode = (PWNODE_HEADER)GuidObject->HiPriority.Buffer;
2534  WmipSetHighWord(ObjectArray[i].NextWnode->Version,
2535  GuidObject->HiPriority.EventsLost);
2536  GuidObject->HiPriority.EventsLost = 0;
2537  WmipAssert(ObjectArray[i].NextWnode != NULL);
2538  } else {
2539  ObjectArray[i].NextWnode = NULL;
2540  }
2541  } else {
2542  if ((GuidObject->LoPriority.Buffer != 0) &&
2543  (GuidObject->LoPriority.NextOffset != 0))
2544  {
2545  ObjectArray[i].NextWnode = (PWNODE_HEADER)GuidObject->LoPriority.Buffer;
2546  WmipSetHighWord(ObjectArray[i].NextWnode->Version,
2547  GuidObject->LoPriority.EventsLost);
2548  GuidObject->LoPriority.EventsLost = 0;
2549  WmipAssert(ObjectArray[i].NextWnode != NULL);
2550  } else {
2551  ObjectArray[i].NextWnode = NULL;
2552  }
2553  }
2554  }
2555 
2556  //
2557  // loop until all events in all guid objects have been
2558  // processed
2559  //
2560  SizeUsed = 0;
2561  Earliest = 0;
2562  OutWnode = NULL;
2563  while (Earliest != 0xffffffff)
2564  {
2565  Timestamp.QuadPart = 0x7fffffffffffffff;
2566  Earliest = 0xffffffff;
2567  for (i = 0; i < HandleCount; i++)
2568  {
2569  InWnode = (PWNODE_HEADER)ObjectArray[i].NextWnode;
2570  if ((InWnode != NULL) &&
2571  (InWnode->TimeStamp.QuadPart < Timestamp.QuadPart))
2572  {
2573  //
2574  // We found an event that is earlier than any previous
2575  // one so we remember the new candidate for earliest
2576  // event and also the previous early event
2577  //
2578  LastTimestamp = Timestamp;
2579  Timestamp = InWnode->TimeStamp;
2580  Earliest = i;
2581  }
2582  }
2583 
2584  if (Earliest != 0xffffffff)
2585  {
2586  //
2587  // We found the earliest event so copy it into the output
2588  // buffer
2589  //
2590  InWnode = (PWNODE_HEADER)ObjectArray[Earliest].NextWnode;
2591  Size = (InWnode->BufferSize + 7) & ~7;
2592 
2593  OutWnode = (PWNODE_HEADER)OutBuffer;
2594  RtlCopyMemory(OutWnode, InWnode, InWnode->BufferSize);
2595  OutWnode->Linkage = Size;
2596 
2597  OutBuffer += Size;
2598  SizeUsed += Size;
2599 
2600  if (InWnode->Linkage != 0)
2601  {
2602  InWnode = (PWNODE_HEADER)((PUCHAR)InWnode + InWnode->Linkage);
2603  } else {
2604  InWnode = NULL;
2605  }
2606  ObjectArray[Earliest].NextWnode = InWnode;
2607  }
2608  }
2609 
2610  *LastWnode = OutWnode;
2611  *OutBufferSizeUsed = SizeUsed;
2612 
2613  //
2614  // clean up event queue resources and reset the object
2615  //
2616  for (i = 0; i < HandleCount; i++)
2617  {
2618 
2619  GuidObject = ObjectArray[i].GuidObject;
2620 
2621  if (IsHiPriority)
2622  {
2623  EventQueue = &GuidObject->HiPriority;
2624  } else {
2625  EventQueue = &GuidObject->LoPriority;
2626  }
2627 
2628  if (EventQueue->Buffer != NULL)
2629  {
2630  WmipFree(EventQueue->Buffer);
2631  EventQueue->Buffer = NULL;
2632  EventQueue->NextOffset = 0;
2633  EventQueue->LastWnode = NULL;
2634  }
2635 
2636  KeClearEvent(&GuidObject->Event);
2637  }
2638 }

2713 NTSTATUS WmipReceiveNotifications(

2717  )

2720  ULONG i;
2721  PWMIGUIDOBJECT GuidObject;

2725  OBJECT_EVENT_INFO StaticObjects[MANY_NOTIFICATION_OBJECTS];

2729  PWNODE_HEADER LastWnode;
2730  PLIST_ENTRY IrpListHead, ThreadListHead;

2746

2750  HandleArray = ReceiveNotification->Handles;

2754  //
2755 
2756  if (HandleCount > MANY_NOTIFICATION_OBJECTS)
2757  {
2758  ObjectArray = WmipAlloc(HandleCount * sizeof(OBJECT_EVENT_INFO));
2759  if (ObjectArray == NULL)
2760  {
2761  return(STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES);
2762  }

2765  }

2768 #endif

2772  // and that the object is not already associated with an irp.
2773  // Also check if there are any hi or lo priority events
2774  //
2775  WmipEnterSMCritSection();
2776 
2777  IsLoPriorityEvent = 0;
2778  IsHighPriorityEvent = 0;
2779  ReplacingIrp = 0;
2780  HiTotalSizeNeeded = 0;
2781  LoTotalSizeNeeded = 0;
2782  ObjectCount = 0;
2783  for (i = 0; (i < HandleCount); i++)
2784  {
2785  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle(HandleArray[i].Handle,
2786  WMIGUID_NOTIFICATION,
2787  WmipGuidObjectType,
2788  UserMode,
2789  &GuidObject,
2790  NULL);
2791  if (! NT_SUCCESS(Status))
2792  {
2793  //
2794  // If one handle is bad then it spoils the whole request
2795  //
2796  //
2797  // Now try with Trace flags and if succeeds,
2798  // We need to make sure the object is a trace request object.
2799  //
2800 
2801  Status = ObReferenceObjectByHandle(HandleArray[i].Handle,
2802  TRACELOG_REGISTER_GUIDS,

2804  UserMode,
2805  &GuidObject,

2807

2809  {

2811  }
2812 
2813  if (! (GuidObject->Flags & WMIGUID_FLAG_REQUEST_OBJECT) )
2814  {
2815  ObDereferenceObject(GuidObject);
2816  Status = STATUS_ACCESS_DENIED;
2817  goto Cleanup;

2819 
2820  }
2821

2823  // Check that we do not have a duplicate object in the list
2824  //
2825  DuplicateObject = FALSE;
2826  for (j = 0; j < ObjectCount; j++)
2827  {
2828  if (GuidObject == ObjectArray[j].GuidObject)
2829  {

2831  "WMI: Duplicate object %p passed to WmiReceiveNotifciations\n",
2832  GuidObject));
2833  ObDereferenceObject(GuidObject);
2834  DuplicateObject = TRUE;
2835  break;
2836  }
2837  }
2838 
2839  if (! DuplicateObject)
2840  {
2841  //
2842  // See if there was an irp attached to the guid object
2843  // already. We'll need to cancel it if all guid objects
2844  // are valid
2845  //
2846  if (GuidObject->Irp != NULL)
2847  {
2848  ReplacingIrp = 1;
2849  }
2850 
2851 
2852  //
2853  // We note if there are any lo and hi priority events
2854  //
2855  ObjectArray[ObjectCount++].GuidObject = GuidObject;
2856 
2857  if (WmipHaveHiPriorityEvent(GuidObject))
2858  {
2859  IsHighPriorityEvent = 1;
2860  }
2861 
2862  if (WmipHaveLoPriorityEvent(GuidObject))
2863  {
2864  IsLoPriorityEvent = 1;
2865  }
2866 
2867  //
2868  // Clean up object in case it was part of a thread list
2869  //
2870  if (GuidObject->EventQueueAction == RECEIVE_ACTION_CREATE_THREAD)
2871  {
2872  WmipAssert(ReplacingIrp == 0);
2873  WmipClearObjectFromThreadList(GuidObject);
2874  }
2875 
2876  //
2877  // Calculate size needed to return data for this guid
2878  //
2879  HiTotalSizeNeeded += ((GuidObject->HiPriority.NextOffset + 7) & ~7);
2880  LoTotalSizeNeeded += ((GuidObject->LoPriority.NextOffset + 7) & ~7);
2881  }
2882  }
2883 
2884  //
2885  // This is the total size needed to return all events
2886  //
2887  SizeNeeded = HiTotalSizeNeeded + LoTotalSizeNeeded;
2888 
2889 
2890  //
2891  // If any of the guid objects already had an irp attached then
2892  // we need to complete that irp with an error and move on
2893  //
2894  if (ReplacingIrp == 1)
2895  {
2896  for (i = 0; i < ObjectCount; i++)
2897  {
2898  GuidObject = ObjectArray[i].GuidObject;
2899  if (GuidObject->Irp != NULL)
2900  {
2901  WmipCompleteGuidIrpWithError(GuidObject);
2902  }
2903  }
2904  }

2907  {
2908  if (SizeNeeded <= MaxBufferSize)
2909  {
2910  //
2911  // There are events waiting to be received so pull them all
2912  // out, high priority ones first then low priority ones. // events will show up first.
2913  //
2914  OutBuffer = (PUCHAR)ReceiveNotification;
2915  LastWnode = NULL;
2916  SizeLeft = MaxBufferSize;
2917  SizeUsed = 0;
2918 
2919  if (IsHighPriorityEvent != 0)
2920  {
2921  WmipCopyFromEventQueues(ObjectArray,
2922  ObjectCount,
2923  OutBuffer,
2924  &SizeUsed,
2925  &LastWnode,
2926  TRUE);
2927 
2928  WmipAssert(SizeUsed <= SizeLeft);
2929  WmipAssert(SizeUsed = HiTotalSizeNeeded);
2930 
2931  OutBuffer += SizeUsed;
2932  SizeLeft -= SizeUsed;
2933  }
2934 
2935  if (IsLoPriorityEvent != 0)
2936  {
2937  WmipAssert(SizeLeft >= LoTotalSizeNeeded);
2938 
2939  WmipCopyFromEventQueues(ObjectArray,
2940  ObjectCount,
2941  OutBuffer,
2942  &SizeUsed,
2943  &LastWnode,
2944  FALSE);
2945 
2946  WmipAssert(SizeUsed <= SizeLeft);
2947  WmipAssert(SizeUsed == LoTotalSizeNeeded);
2948 
2949  SizeLeft -= SizeUsed;
2950  }
2951 
2952  //
2953  // We need to set the linkage field for the last wnode in
2954  // the list to 0 so it can mark the end of the list
2955  // correctly
2956  //
2957  if (LastWnode != NULL)
2958  {
2959  LastWnode->Linkage = 0;
2960  }
2961 
2962  //
2963  // Compute the number of bytes used to fill the output
2964  // buffer by subtracting the size left from the size passed
2965  // in
2966  //
2967  *OutBufferSize = MaxBufferSize - SizeLeft;
2968  } else {
2969  //
2970  // Not enough room to return all of the event data so we return

3984 NTSTATUS WmipWriteWnodeToObject(
3985  PWMIGUIDOBJECT Object,
3986  PWNODE_HEADER Wnode,
3987  BOOLEAN IsHighPriority
3988 )
3989 /*+++
3990 
3991 Routine Description:
3992 
3993  This routine will write a WNODE into the queue of events to be returned
3994  for a guid object. If there is an irp already waiting then it will be
3995  satisfied with the event otherwise it will be queued in the objects
3996  buffer.
3997 
3998  This routine assumes that the SM Critical section is held
3999 
4000 Arguments:
4001 
4002  Object is the object to which to send the request
4003 
4004  Wnode is the Wnode with the event
4005 
4006  IsHighPriority is TRUE if the event should go into the high priority
4007  queue
4008 
4009 Return Value:
4010 
4011  STATUS_SUCCESS or an error code
4012 
4013 ---*/
4014 {
4015  PIRP Irp;
4016  ULONG WnodeSize;
4017  PUCHAR OutBuffer;
4018  ULONG OutBufferSize;
4019  PIO_STACK_LOCATION IrpStack;
4020  PWNODE_TOO_SMALL WnodeTooSmall;
4021  NTSTATUS Status;
4022 
4023  PAGED_CODE();
4024 
4025  //
4026  // Someone has registered to receive this event so
4027  // see if there is an irp waiting to be completed or
4028  // if we should just queue it
4029  //
4030  Irp = Object->Irp;
4031  if ((Irp != NULL) &&
4032  (IoSetCancelRoutine(Irp, NULL)))
4033  {
4034  //
4035  // There is an irp waiting for this event, copy out the
4036  // event and complete the irp
4037  //
4038  IrpStack = IoGetCurrentIrpStackLocation(Irp);
4039  OutBuffer = Irp->AssociatedIrp.SystemBuffer;
4040  OutBufferSize = IrpStack->Parameters.DeviceIoControl.OutputBufferLength;
4041  WnodeSize = Wnode->BufferSize;
4042  if (WnodeSize > OutBufferSize)
4043  {
4044  //
4045  // There is not enough room to return the event so
4046  // we return a WNODE_TOO_SMALL with the size needed
4047  // and then go and queue the event
4048  //
4049  WmipAssert(OutBufferSize >= sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL));
4050  WnodeTooSmall = (PWNODE_TOO_SMALL)OutBuffer;
4051  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.BufferSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
4052  WnodeTooSmall->WnodeHeader.Flags = WNODE_FLAG_TOO_SMALL;
4053  WnodeTooSmall->SizeNeeded = WnodeSize;
4054  WnodeSize = sizeof(WNODE_TOO_SMALL);
4055  Status = WmipQueueEventToObject(Object,
4056  Wnode,
4057  IsHighPriority);
4058  } else {
4059  //
4060  // Plenty of room, copy the event into the irp
4061  // buffer and complete the irp
4062  //
4063  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_EVENT_INFO_LEVEL,
4064  "WMI: Returning event to waiting irp for object %p\n", Object));
4065  RtlCopyMemory(OutBuffer, Wnode, WnodeSize);
4066  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4067  }
4068 
4069  //
4070  // Remove link from all objects associated with the irp
4071  // since now the irp is going away.
4072  //
4073  WmipClearIrpObjectList(Irp);
4074  Irp->IoStatus.Information = WnodeSize;
4075  Irp->IoStatus.Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4076  IoCompleteRequest(Irp, IO_NO_INCREMENT);
4077  } else {
4078  //
4079  // There is no irp waiting to receive the event so we
4080  // need to queue it if we can
4081  //
4082  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_EVENT_INFO_LEVEL,
4083  "WMI: Queued event to object %p\n", Object));
4084  Status = WmipQueueEventToObject(Object,
4085  Wnode,
4086  IsHighPriority);
4087  }
4088 
4089  return(Status);
4090 }

4093 NTSTATUS WmipProcessEvent(
4094  PWNODE_HEADER InWnode,
4095  BOOLEAN IsHighPriority,
4096  BOOLEAN FreeBuffer
4097  )
4098 {
4099  LPGUID Guid;
4100  NTSTATUS Status, ReturnStatus;
4101  PBGUIDENTRY GuidEntry;
4102  PLIST_ENTRY ObjectList, ObjectListNext;
4103  PWMIGUIDOBJECT Object;
4104  LPGUID EventGuid = &InWnode->Guid;
4105  PWNODE_HEADER Wnode, WnodeTarget;
4106 
4107  PAGED_CODE();
4108 
4109  //
4110  // If the event references a guid that needs to be queried then
4111  // go do the dereferencing here.
4112  //
4113  if (InWnode->Flags & WNODE_FLAG_EVENT_REFERENCE)
4114  {
4115  WnodeTarget = WmipDereferenceEvent(InWnode);
4116  if (WnodeTarget == NULL)
4117  {
4118  if (FreeBuffer)
4119  {
4120  ExFreePool(InWnode);
4121  }
4122  return(STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL);
4123  }
4124  Wnode = WnodeTarget;
4125  } else {
4126  Wnode = InWnode;
4127  WnodeTarget = NULL;
4128  }
4129 
4130  //
4131  // Be sure to use the guid of the referenced event, not the event that
4132  // was originally fired.
4133  EventGuid = &Wnode->Guid;
4134 
4135 
4136  //
4137  // If it is Trace error notification, disable providers
4138  //
4139  if (IsEqualGUID(EventGuid, & TraceErrorGuid)) {
4140  PWMI_TRACE_EVENT WmiEvent = (PWMI_TRACE_EVENT) InWnode;
4141  ULONG LoggerId = WmiGetLoggerId(InWnode->HistoricalContext);
4142  if ( InWnode->BufferSize >= sizeof(WMI_TRACE_EVENT) ) {
4143  //
4144  // Logger thread terminating will result in DisableTrace
4145  // through StopTrace. No need to call twice.
4146  //
4147  if (WmiEvent->TraceErrorFlag == STATUS_SEVERITY_ERROR) {
4148  WmipDisableTraceProviders(LoggerId);
4149  }
4150  }
4151  }
4152 
4153  //
4154  // See if this event has a static name and if so fill it in
4155  if (Wnode->Flags & WNODE_FLAG_STATIC_INSTANCE_NAMES)
4156  {
4157  Wnode = WmipIncludeStaticNames(Wnode);
4158  }
4159 
4160  //
4161  // See if any data provider has registered this event
4162  //
4163  WmipDebugPrintEx((DPFLTR_WMICORE_ID, DPFLTR_EVENT_INFO_LEVEL,
4164  "WMI: Received event\n"));
4165  Guid = &Wnode->Guid;
4166  GuidEntry = WmipFindGEByGuid(Guid, TRUE);
4167  if (GuidEntry != NULL)
4168  {
4169  //
4170  // Yup, so check if there are any open objects to the guid and
4171  // if anyone is interested in receiving events from them
4172  //
4173  ReturnStatus = STATUS_SUCCESS;
4174  WmipEnterSMCritSection();
4175  ObjectList = GuidEntry->ObjectHead.Flink;
4176  while (ObjectList != &GuidEntry->ObjectHead)
4177  {
4178  Object = CONTAINING_RECORD(ObjectList,
4179  WMIGUIDOBJECT,
4180  GEObjectList);
4181 
4182  //
4183  // ObRefSafe so that we can be sure that the object is not
4184  // in the process of being deleted. If this function
4185  // returns FALSE then the object is being deleted and so we
4186  // don't want to use it. If TRUE then it is safe to use the
4187  // object
4188  //
4189  ObjectListNext = ObjectList->Flink;
4190  if (ObReferenceObjectSafe(Object))
4191  {
4192  //
4193  // Make sure the object has not been marked as one that
4194  // should not receive any events since it is
4195  // transitioning to a closed state
4196  //
4197  if ((Object->Flags & WMIGUID_FLAG_RECEIVE_NO_EVENTS) == 0)
4198  {
4199  if (Object->Flags & WMIGUID_FLAG_KERNEL_NOTIFICATION)
4200  {
4201  //
4202  // KM clients get a direct callback
4203  //
4204  WMI_NOTIFICATION_CALLBACK Callback;
4205  PVOID Context;
4206 
4207  Callback = Object->Callback;
4208  Context = Object->CallbackContext;
4209  if (Callback != NULL)
4210  {
4211  (*Callback)(Wnode, Context);
4212  }
4213  } else {
4214  //
4215  // UM clients get event written into IRP or queued up
4216  //
4217  Status = WmipWriteWnodeToObject(Object,
4218  Wnode,
4219  IsHighPriority);
4220 
4221  if (! NT_SUCCESS(Status))
4222  {
4223  //
4224  // If any attempts to queue the event fail then we return
4225  // an error
4226  //
4227  ReturnStatus = STATUS_UNSUCCESSFUL;
4228  }
4229  }
4230  }
4231 
4232  ObDereferenceObject(Object);
4233  //
4234  // Note that we cannot touch the object anymore
4235  //
4236  }
4237 
4238  ObjectList = ObjectListNext;
4239  }
4240 
4241  WmipLeaveSMCritSection();
4242  WmipUnreferenceGE(GuidEntry);
4243  } else {
4244  ReturnStatus = STATUS_WMI_GUID_NOT_FOUND;
4245  }
4246 
4247  if (FreeBuffer)
4248  {
4249  //
4250  // Free buffer passed by driver containing event
4251  //
4252  ExFreePool(InWnode);
4253  }
4254 
4255  if ((Wnode != InWnode) && (Wnode != WnodeTarget))
4256  {
4257  //
4258  // If we inserted static names then free it
4259  //
4260  WmipFree(Wnode);
4261  }
4262 
4263  if (WnodeTarget != NULL)
4264  {
4265  //
4266  // if we dereferenced then free it
4267  //
4268  WmipFree(WnodeTarget);
4269  }
4270 
4271  return(ReturnStatus);
4272 }

4495 NTSTATUS WmipWriteMBToObject(
4496  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT RequestObject,
4497  IN PWMIGUIDOBJECT ReplyObject,
4498  IN PUCHAR Message,
4499  IN ULONG MessageSize
4500  )
4501 /*+++
4502 
4503 Routine Description:
4504 
4505  This routine will build a WNODE out of a message and then write it
4506  into the Request object. If a reply object is specified then the reply
4507  object is linked into the request object so when the reply is written
4508  to the request object it can be routed to the reply object correctly,.
4509 
4510  This routine assumes that the SM Critical section is held
4511 
4512 Arguments:
4513 
4514  RequestObject is the object to which to send the request
4515 
4516  ReplyObject is the object to which the request object should reply.
4517  This may be NULL in the case that no reply is needed.
4518 
4519  Message is the message to be sent
4520 
4521  MessageSize is the size of the message in bytes
4522 
4523 Return Value:
4524 
4525  STATUS_SUCCESS or an error code
4526 
4527 ---*/
4528 {
4529  PWNODE_HEADER Wnode;
4530  ULONG WnodeSize;
4531  PUCHAR Payload;
4532  ULONG i;
4533  PMBREQUESTS MBRequest;
4534  NTSTATUS Status;
4535 
4536  PAGED_CODE();
4537 
4538  //
4539  // Allocate space to build a wnode out of the data passed
4540  //
4541  WnodeSize = sizeof(WNODE_HEADER) + MessageSize;
4542  Wnode = WmipAlloc(WnodeSize);
4543  if (Wnode != NULL)
4544  {
4545  //
4546  // Create an internal wnode with the message as the payload
4547  //
4548  RtlZeroMemory(Wnode, sizeof(WNODE_HEADER));
4549  Wnode->BufferSize = WnodeSize;
4550  Wnode->Flags = WNODE_FLAG_INTERNAL;
4551  Wnode->Guid = RequestObject->Guid;
4552  Wnode->ProviderId = WmiMBRequest;
4553  Payload = (PUCHAR)Wnode + sizeof(WNODE_HEADER);
4554  RtlCopyMemory(Payload, Message, MessageSize);
4555 
4556  //
4557  // if this request requires a reply then update the lists for the
4558  // request and reply objects
4559  //
4560  if (ReplyObject != NULL)
4561  {
4562  //
4563  // Find a free spot in the request object to link
4564  // in the reply.
4565  //
4566  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4567 
4568  for (i = 0; i < MAXREQREPLYSLOTS; i++)
4569  {
4570  MBRequest = &RequestObject->MBRequests[i];
4571  if (MBRequest->ReplyObject == NULL)
4572  {
4573  //
4574  // We have a free slot so link request and reply
4575  // objects together and send off the request.
4576  // The request object takes a ref count on the reply
4577  // object since it maintains a pointer to it. The
4578  // refcount is released when the request object writes
4579  // the reply back to the reply object.
4580  //
4581  Status = ObReferenceObjectByPointer(ReplyObject,
4582  0,
4583  WmipGuidObjectType,
4584  KernelMode);
4585 
4586  if (NT_SUCCESS(Status))
4587  {
4588  MBRequest->ReplyObject = ReplyObject;
4589  InsertTailList(&ReplyObject->RequestListHead,
4590  &MBRequest->RequestListEntry);
4591 
4592  Wnode->Version = i;
4593 
4594  Status = WmipWriteWnodeToObject(RequestObject,
4595  Wnode,
4596  TRUE);
4597  if (! NT_SUCCESS(Status))
4598  {
4599  //
4600  // If writing request failed, we need to cleanup
4601  //
4602  ObDereferenceObject(ReplyObject);
4603  MBRequest->ReplyObject = NULL;
4604  RemoveEntryList(&MBRequest->RequestListEntry);
4605  }
4606  }
4607  break;
4608  }
4609  }
4610  } else {
4611  //
4612  // No reply required so we just write the message to the
4613  // object and continue with our business
4614  //
4615  Status = WmipWriteWnodeToObject(RequestObject,
4616  Wnode,
4617  TRUE);
4618  }
4619 
4620  WmipFree(Wnode);
4621  } else {
4622  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
4623  }
4624  return(Status);
4625 }

4633 )

4654

4658 
4659  STATUS_SUCCESS or an error code
4660

4702  (*WrittenCount)++;
4703  }
4704  }
4705

4708
